{
  "text": "Once the detailed mechanism was reduced to the minimum acceptable size, the mechanism was reduced further by lumping the isomers of R, RO 2 , QOOH, O 2 QOOH and C 10 KET into a lumped species. One isomer was chosen to represent the thermodynamic properties of the lumped species. Rate constants for each major reaction pathway and lumped species in Figure 2 were assigned. Following the detailed TPGME mechanism, the rates of H-abstraction form TPGME by radicals such as OH, H and O were taken by analogy with those for 1-and 2-butanol from Sarathy et al., [CITATION_1] except for sites involving a methyl group where Sarathy et al. [CITATION_2] were used. For the low-temperature reactions of TPGME, the reaction rate constants were drawn from reaction rate rules in the butanol and alkane mechanisms of Sarathy et al. [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] as done for the detailed model.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "95742113",
    "[CITATION_2]": "98785165",
    "[CITATION_3]": "95742113",
